Vehement/Sun Crusher/Reflector:




Vehement watched the darkness suddenly disperse as light flooded into the CR 
chamber.  The nine foot tall Vehement stepped out of the CR chamber, heading 
for the bridge.

Vehement arrived on the bridge, looking to his two soldiers.
&quot;What have you found so far?&quot;

&quot;Well, Archbishop, there are several bases.  There is an area where two bases 
are together.  I believe that&#39;s where the strongest faction resides.  It&#39;s on 
an island also, and I&#39;m detecting over twenty-five different energy 
sigantures.&quot;

&quot;Hmmm...that&#39;s many for Earth.  I&#39;m surprised.&quot; Vehement replied.  &quot;Go on.  
Is anyone near us?  Where are we?&quot;

&quot;We are in what will be known as Ulaanbaator, Mongolia in the Gobi Desert in 
the continent of Asia.  There is no one that close to us.  We are surrounded 
by complete desert.&quot;

Vehement looked to Reflector and Sun Crusher.  &quot;Open up a comm. transmission 
to ALL frequencies.  I will speak.&quot;

&quot;Yes, Archbishop.&quot; Reflector replied, going to his terminal and pressing in a 
few commands.



&quot;Attention, all residents of Past Earth.  I am Vehement.  My battlecruiser 
has crashed on this planet as I&#39;m sure you know by now.  My base is badly 
damaged and is in need of serious repair.  Any assistance would be thankful.&quot; 
he signaled Reflector to end the transmission.  &quot;Play that continously for 
five mega-cycles.&quot;

&quot;Yes, sir.&quot; Sun Crusher said, walking over to Reflector&#39;s terminal and 
pressing a few commands.  &quot;Done.&quot;

&quot;Good.  What is the status of the base?&quot;

&quot;Surprisingly,&quot; Sun Crusher said with a smile, &quot;all weapons are intact, all 
CR pools and chambers are fully functional, and our shields and other primary 
systems are intact.  Energy reserves are down to 74% though, and there are 
several breaches in the hull.&quot;

&quot;How long would it take to repair the hull?&quot;

&quot;A mega-cycle.  They aren&#39;t bad.&quot;

&quot;Do we have any solar panels?&quot;  

&quot;Yes.&quot;

&quot;Good.  Set those up.&quot;

&quot;It&#39;ll take two mega-cycles.&quot;

&quot;Alright, I&#39;ll keep defenses active while you do that.&quot;

&quot;Understood.&quot; Sun Crusher acknowledge, him and Reflector walking out of the 
bridge.

Vehement sat in his command chair, smiling as the transmission continuously 
played to all bases and everyone on Earth.
